  card StrPhysical, then: StrSymptoms do
    text("Physical Symptoms:
    ‚Ä¢	Headaches: Persistent headaches, often tension-related, can be a physical manifestation of stress.
    ‚Ä¢	Muscle Tension: Chronic stress can lead to muscle tension and aches, particularly in the neck, shoulders, and back.
    ‚Ä¢	Fatigue: Feeling constantly tired, even after adequate rest, is a common symptom of stress.
    ‚Ä¢	Digestive Issues: Stress can cause stomach discomfort, bloating, constipation, or diarrhea.
    ‚Ä¢	Insomnia: Difficulty falling or staying asleep due to racing thoughts and worries.
    ‚Ä¢	Rapid Heartbeat: Stress can increase heart rate and sometimes lead to palpitations.
    ")
  end
  card StrEmotional, then: StrSymptoms do
    text("Emotional Symptoms:
    ‚Ä¢	Irritability: Feeling easily annoyed, agitated, or frustrated, even over minor issues.
    ‚Ä¢	Mood Swings: Frequent and abrupt changes in mood, from feeling happy to suddenly becoming sad or angry.
    ‚Ä¢	Anxiety: Constant worry, restlessness, or a feeling of impending doom.
    ‚Ä¢	Depression: Persistent sadness, feelings of hopelessness, and a lack of interest in activities.
    ‚Ä¢	Feeling Overwhelmed: Being unable to cope with normal stressors and feeling constantly overwhelmed.
    ‚Ä¢	Sense of Isolation: Feeling detached from others, even when surrounded by people.
    ")
  end
  card StrCognitive, then: StrSymptoms do
    text("Cognitive Symptoms:
    ‚Ä¢	Difficulty Concentrating: Finding it hard to focus, make decisions, or complete tasks.
    ‚Ä¢	Forgetfulness: Experiencing memory lapses and forgetfulness, especially regarding recent events.
    ‚Ä¢	Negative Thinking: Pervasive negative thoughts about oneself, situations, or the future.
    ‚Ä¢	Intrusive Thoughts: Repetitive and distressing thoughts or images that are difficult to control.
    ")
  end
  card StrBehavioral, then: StrSymptoms do
    text("Behavioral Symptoms:
    ‚Ä¢	Changes in Eating Patterns: Stress can lead to overeating or loss of appetite.
    ‚Ä¢	Increased Use of Substances: Escalating use of alcohol, tobacco, or drugs as a way to cope.
    ‚Ä¢	Social Withdrawal: Avoiding social interactions and isolating oneself from friends and family.
    ‚Ä¢	Procrastination: Delaying tasks and responsibilities due to feeling overwhelmed.
    ‚Ä¢	Restlessness: Fidgeting, pacing, or an inability to relax due to inner tension.
    ")
  end
  card StrInterpersonal, then: StrSymptoms do
    text("Interpersonal Symptoms:
    ‚Ä¢	Conflict in Relationships: Increased arguments and disagreements with friends, family, or colleagues.
    ‚Ä¢	Difficulty in Communication: Struggling to express thoughts and feelings clearly, leading to misunderstandings.
    ")
  end

